## <a id="delete-instances"></a> Delete Service Instances

<%= vars.product_short %> enables you to either delete individual service instances
or delete multiple service instances based on a search or filter.

<p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong>
  <%= vars.product_short %> does not allow you to delete a service instance with
  service bindings, service keys, or route associations.
</p>

**To delete an individual service instance:**

1. Click the service instance that you want to delete.
1. Click **DELETE** at the bottom-right of the service instance card.
1. Click **DELETE** in the warning pop-up.
<br><br>

**To delete multiple service instances:**

1. Filter for the service instances that you want to delete.
For instructions, see [Filter Service Instances](#filter-instances).

1. Click **DELETE ALL**.

    ![screenshot shows a filtered list of service instances with the delete button highlighted](multi-delete.png)

    <p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong>
      If any service instances in your filter have bindings or service keys,
      <%= vars.product_short %> displays a warning pop-up, which allows you to
      delete only the unbound service instances from your search.</p>

1. Click **DELETE** in the warning pop-up.
